<subSubSection pageId="134" pageNumber="135" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="134" pageNumber="135">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="134" pageNumber="135">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Choisy, Mem. Soc. Phys. Geneve 6: 477. 1834. (Choisy" authorityYear="1834" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus rottlerianus" order="Solanales" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rottlerianus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">Convolvulus rottlerianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has only recently been found in Ethiopia and is unknown in Iran and Arabia. Ethiopian material was described as a separate species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sebsebe Demissew" authorityYear="1999" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus gilbertii" order="Solanales" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gilbertii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">Convolvulus gilbertii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, probably because the possibility of the occurrence of an Indian species was not considered. No difference between specimens from the two areas can be discerned. Little is known about the habitat of this subspecies in India but it is found in drier areas. In Ethiopia it is a rare plant of Acacia bushland.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
